Join the Conversation David Clark , dclark2@cincinna.gannett.com 2:03 p.m. EDT October 11, 2015 
Green Bay Packers cornerback Quinten Rollins. (Photo: Benny Sieu-USA TODAY Sports) 
Former Miami University RedHawks star defensive back and basketball player Quinten Rollins of Wilmington scored his first NFL touchdown on a pick-6 for the Packers against the Rams at Lambeau Field. 
Reactions via Twitter: Rollins' 45-yd pick-six is first INT-TD by a #Packers rookie since Marques Anderson in 2002. #STLvsGB â€” Green Bay Packers (@packers) October 11, 2015 Quinten Rollins with the pick six for the @packers ! Congrats on your first NFL touchdown, @QRollins2 ! #MiamiOH #LoveandHonor
